1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:01,041
Day 10.

2
00:00:01,041 --> 00:00:04,194
I woke up and Twitter had taken my account.

3
00:00:04,194 --> 00:00:05,513
No warning.

4
00:00:05,513 --> 00:00:07,250
No reason given.

5
00:00:07,250 --> 00:00:08,694
I can't code.

6
00:00:08,694 --> 00:00:10,763
9 years in crypto.

7
00:00:10,763 --> 00:00:12,888
AI trades my thousand.

8
00:00:12,888 --> 00:00:13,902
Day 10.

9
00:00:13,902 --> 00:00:25,777
The moment it happened, I realized every thread I'd written, every follower, every receipt I'd posted — all of it, held by one platform that didn't call first.

10
00:00:25,777 --> 00:00:32,444
Same day I did something that sounded unrelated — I launched bilingual mode on my own website.

11
00:00:32,444 --> 00:00:34,527
At the time it felt small.

12
00:00:34,527 --> 00:00:38,777
The week I had nowhere else to speak, it stopped feeling small.

13
00:00:38,777 --> 00:00:47,125
There's a sentence I'd heard for years and always dismissed as cheesy — don't build your most valuable thing on top of ground you don't own.

14
00:00:47,125 --> 00:00:51,151
That day, that sentence became an invoice.

15
00:00:51,151 --> 00:00:54,625
From Day 10 on — my own site is home base.

16
00:00:54,625 --> 00:00:57,805
Every other platform is just distribution.

17
00:00:57,805 --> 00:01:00,902
The kind that can be turned off at any time.

18
00:01:00,902 --> 00:01:07,069
Day 11 tomorrow — I wrote the full story of Trade number 267.

19
00:01:07,069 --> 00:01:08,500
Follow along.

